{
  "id": "k-vI8epC",
  "data": {
    "guidelines": [
      {
        "id": "D1oE0NvYfS",
        "type": "do",
        "content": {
          "type": "doc",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "text": "Heading",
                  "type": "text",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "bold"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "text": "Succinctly communicate what happened.",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "text": "Message",
                  "type": "text",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "bold"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "text": "Remember you're having a conversation with a human. Lean into our empathetic and transparent voice when the user needs to decide what to do next. ",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "text": "Actions",
                  "type": "text",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "bold"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "text": "If the primary action is a negative one such as \"Discard,\" the secondary action must be semantically distinct from the primary action. ",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "text": "\"Keep editing / Discard\" are a good example of two semantically distinct actions. They give clear guidance for each of the actions in relation to the user's context. ",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "text": " ",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "doPEyP6rD",
        "type": "dont",
        "content": {
          "type": "doc",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "text": "Heading",
                  "type": "text",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "bold"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "text": "Don't assume they know what happened. Asking a question is more suitable if the user initiate the action themselves.  ",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "text": "Message",
                  "type": "text",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "bold"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "text": "Don't say \"Are you sure?\" especially when they may not be aware of what happened.  ",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "text": "Don't repeat the heading. ",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "text": "Actions",
                  "type": "text",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "bold"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "text": "Don't use \"Cancel.\" ",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "text": "Because \"Cancel / Discard\" are semantically similar, the user may interpret \"Cancel\" as \"canceling the unsaved changes.\" This can create confusion. ",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      }
    ],
    "tileStyles": {
      "imageSize": "none"
    }
  },
  "blockType": "guidelines"
}
